<subSubSection pageNumber="359" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="359">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Note:</emphasis>
Conservation of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Briza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Briza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Briza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">B. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a conserved type was proposed by Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 556. 1992). However, in discussion within the Committee for Spermatophyta, it became clear that the proposed type would conflict with the infrageneric nomenclature adopted by Tzvelev, and so the Committee did not approve conservation (see 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Taxon</emphasis>
44: 612. 1995).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
